---
import Heading from "../components/ui/Heading.astro"
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Colophon"
  description="How this site is built — the stack, design decisions, and technical details."
>
  <Heading level="h2" as="h1" class="mt-6 mb-6">Colophon</Heading>

  <p class="text-muted-foreground text-sm mb-6">
    A page about the making of this website. The stack, the decisions, and the
    philosophy behind it. Following the
    <a href="https://indieweb.org/colophon" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IndieWeb colophon tradition</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-3">Stack</Heading>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-none pl-0">
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Framework</span>
          <span><a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro 5</a> — static site generation with islands architecture</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Content</span>
          <span>MDX with Astro Content Collections — migrated from Contentlayer</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Styling</span>
          <span>Tailwind CSS v4 with custom design tokens</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">JS sprinkles</span>
          <span>Alpine.js — for theme toggle, dropdown, and search</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Components</span>
          <span>shadcn/ui primitives via Base UI for interactive elements</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Syntax highlighting</span>
          <span>Shiki via rehype-pretty-code — themes matched to site design</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Icons</span>
          <span>Lucide via astro-icon — consistent, minimal, open source</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-3">Typography</Heading>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-none pl-0">
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Body</span>
          <span>System font stack — native rendering, zero layout shift, instant load</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Headings</span>
          <span>Signifier (serif) — adds warmth to headings without sacrificing readability</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Code</span>
          <span>JetBrains Mono — ligatures, clear at small sizes</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-3">Hosting & Infrastructure</Heading>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-none pl-0">
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Hosting</span>
          <span>Vercel — zero-config deploys from git push</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Analytics</span>
          <span>Umami — self-hosted, GDPR-compliant, no cookies</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Newsletter</span>
          <span>Self-hosted instance — no third-party dependency</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
          <span class="text-muted-foreground shrink-0 text-sm w-40">Domain</span>
          <span>yashagarwal.in — personal namespace since 2016</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-3">Design Philosophy</Heading>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-4">
        <li><strong>No JS by default.</strong> Pages are static HTML. JS is a sprinkle — theme toggle, search, and the newsletter form.</li>
        <li><strong>Pure black and white.</strong> No color palette. Just contrast. Content is the color.</li>
        <li><strong>System fonts first.</strong> No webfont downloads for body text. Instant rendering.</li>
        <li><strong>Dark mode via CSS custom properties.</strong> One set of tokens, two themes.</li>
        <li><strong>No tracking, no ads, no popups.</strong> This is a personal site, not a growth engine.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mb-3">History</Heading>
      <p>
        This site has existed in various forms since 2016. It started on Hugo,
        moved to Next.js, and now lives on Astro. Each migration taught me
        something — Hugo was fast but limited, Next.js was powerful but heavy,
        Astro is the sweet spot: static HTML with the option to add interactivity
        where needed.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2">
        The source code is on <a href="https://github.com/yashhere/yashagarwal.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
